Another thing to consider is that yes, gateways do break down.  What
is listed as being your primary address in the host table (oh, sorry,
as given by the nameserver) may not work, due to temporary hardware
problems (but this never happens, right guys) that do not involve
your other addresses.

Also, some routes may be faster than others - for example, we (lll-crg)
are connected to the rest of the world by two links, a 9.6kbps line
direct to the imp and via an ethernet (well, an ether&lt;multiple magic
black boxes&gt;broadband&lt;MMBBs&gt;ether) and from there via a proteon
gateway (lll-labnet-gw) to the same imp.  

Most of the time, going through the proteon is faster.  However, sometimes
it or one of the MMBBs imbetween us and it goes down (or the techs take
something down "just for a little while" to replace something without
telling us (I detect an error in the AE-35 unit)).  

Unfortunately, the Berklix software doesn't try all the alternate
addresses listed in the host table if one set doesn't work.  For that
matter, nor does it try other routes if one router is down.  Boo hiss.

	andy

